    • calculateProductionTotals

      public void calculateProductionTotals()
      Calculates and displays the total quantity of materials and the number of times each operation is performed in the production process. This method traverses the production tree recursively to gather the required data. complexity O(N + M + O) - O(N): Traverses the entire production tree with N nodes. - O(M): Iterates through the materials map, where M is the number of distinct materials. - O(O): Iterates through the operations map, where O is the number of distinct operations.

    • getQualityCheckSequence

      public Queue<QualityCheck> getQualityCheckSequence()
      Generates a priority queue of quality checks based on the production tree. Quality checks are prioritized by their level in the production process, with higher levels indicating higher priority.
      Returns:
      A priority queue containing quality checks ordered by priority level. Time Complexity: O(N log N) The method goes through each node (O(N)) and adds each "Operation" to the priority queue (O(log N)).

    • updateNodeQuantityWithCascade

      public String updateNodeQuantityWithCascade(String identifier, double newQuantity)
      Updates a node's quantity and handles cascading updates to related nodes.
      Parameters:
      identifier - The ID or name of the node to update
      newQuantity - The new quantity to set
      Returns:
      A string describing all updates made Metodo Principal (updateNodeQuantityWithCascade): A busca inicial do nó é O(n) no pior caso (quando procura por nome) A construção da resposta é O(m) onde m é o número de nós atualizados Complexidade das Operações em Cascata: cascadeUp: O(h * s) onde: h é a altura da árvore s é o número médio de irmãos (siblings) por nó cascadeDown: O(d) onde: d é o número total de descendentes do nó sendo atualizado Complexidade Total: No pior caso: O(n + h*s + d) onde n é o número total de nós na árvore
